>after exploring the expanse of space for decades humanity finally found other intelligent life
>a race of anthropomorphic animals like that of earth which greatly confused scientists as to how they evolved much the same way, with the closest thing to a human being more bipedal monkeys
>these ‘anthros’ had developed primitive civilisations similar to ancient humans
>however unlike humans these civilisations were matriarchal in nature, with the females having control over the male population
>after great a debate over rights and laws that didn’t yet exist it was decided the planet they lived on would be colonised and brought into the United Human Federation (UHF)
>the name was called xenophobic of course by some now aliens were being brought into it.

>so to try and make this colonisation of an entire planet easier envoys we’re sent to bring members of as many nations as possible back to earth to learn their cultures and what-not
>however every member of these envoys were female, due to the matriarchal society’s
>before these envoys had even gotten halfway through the journey back to earth though each race, human and anthro were quickly learning a lot about one another
>ship repairmen and mechanics learnt their space ships air ducts needed to be bolted shut, lest a curious rodent like anthro decide to explore them, leading to several of them accidentally electrocuting themselves and having to take a visit to the medical deck.
>this also meant captains had to make awkward announcements on why the ships vents were pumping out air that smelt faintly of burnt hair
>although these accidents meant doctors could examine the aliens physiology regularly and more closely
